Cell["\<\
This notebook consists of four chapters \[LineSeparator]\t1. How to use this \
notebook\[LineSeparator]\t2. Load Data \[LineSeparator]\t3. Engine \
\[LineSeparator]\t4. Play \[LineSeparator]First-time users are recommended to \
read Chapter 1 and jump straight to Chapter 4.
Experts interested in tweaking the notebook may modify Chapter 2 or 3 at \
their own risk. \
\>", "Text",
 CellChangeTimes->{{3.988486166898633*^9, 3.988486177489875*^9}, {
   3.988586476866213*^9, 3.988586508433105*^9}, {3.988586557254129*^9, 
   3.988586651043503*^9}, {3.988586769840238*^9, 3.988586780804853*^9}, {
   3.988587442985183*^9, 3.988587462069988*^9}, 
   3.9886617396932917`*^9},ExpressionUUID->"b180a45e-e338-4675-aa99-\
300f123132df"],

Cell["\<\
Chapter 2 (Load Data) requires that the folder [OmegaData] be located in the \
same folder as this notebook. \[LineSeparator]Depending on your computer, It \
may take up to a minute to load the data.\
\>", "Text",
 CellChangeTimes->{{3.9886626038865023`*^9, 3.988662623866106*^9}, {
  3.9886813922016983`*^9, 
  3.9886813962924137`*^9}},ExpressionUUID->"51ae3c0e-e8fc-4def-a8b8-\
e68ef486bb02"],

Cell["\<\
This notebook has two main functions \[LineSeparator]\ta) Retrieving the \
Murua coefficient \[Omega](G) of a given graph. \[LineSeparator]\tb) \
Illustrating how the Murua formula works for a given graph. \
\[LineSeparator]Examples are given in Chapter 4. Readers are encouraged to \
play with more examples. \
\>", "Text",
 CellChangeTimes->{{3.988586723892238*^9, 3.988586855837871*^9}, {
   3.988587417706197*^9, 3.988587432706038*^9}, {3.988681362331876*^9, 
   3.988681370911325*^9}, 
   3.9886814891851788`*^9},ExpressionUUID->"698fe5e0-3c8d-446e-8d62-\
8b6377106e65"],

