dab545a7cbb2"],

Cell["\<\
Have fun playing with the built-in functions. \[LineSeparator]Hopefully, the \
examples below are self-explanatory. \[LineSeparator]\[LineSeparator]We have \
5 main functions. \[LineSeparator]1) wCL: \[Omega](G) in the color basis\
\[LineSeparator]2) wBW: \[Omega](G) in the BW basis
3) Visualise: display the graph, in both bases\[LineSeparator]4) \
MuruaProcedureCL: how Murua formula works in the color \
basis\[LineSeparator]5) MuruaProcedureBW: how Murua formula works in the BW \
basis\
\>", "Text",
 CellChangeTimes->{{3.9885864060068493`*^9, 3.98858643132199*^9}, {
